#Limiting to pertinent columns
chl <- chl %>% 
  select(date, collected, work_area, survey, site_id, line_out_depth,
         filter_type, chla, chla_flag)

#Adding year column
chl <- chl %>% 
  mutate(year = lubridate::year(date),
         month = lubridate::month(date))

#Only including AV and unflagged data
chl_qc <- chl %>% 
  filter(!is.na(chla) & (chla_flag == "AV" | chla_flag == "ADL" | is.na(chla_flag)))

#Removing exact duplicates -  not replicates. Not sure why these are happening
chl_qc <- chl_qc %>% 
  group_by(date, site_id, line_out_depth, filter_type) %>% 
  distinct(.keep_all = TRUE) %>% 
  ungroup()

#separating chl bulk
chl_bulk <- chl_qc %>% 
  filter(filter_type == "Bulk GF/F")

#Pivot Longer - this also calculates the daily mean for a triplcate that was collected.
qu39_tidy <- qu39 %>% 
  pivot_longer(c(Cyan, Hapt, Chlo, Cryp, Dino, Dict, Diat),
                 names_to = "phyto_group", values_to = "TChla") %>% 
  group_by(date, site_id, depth, phyto_group) %>% 
  summarize(TChla_mean = mean(TChla)) %>% 
  ungroup() %>% 
  group_by(date, site_id, depth) %>% 
  mutate(TChla_sum = sum(TChla_mean)) %>% 
  ungroup()
`summarise()` has grouped output by 'date', 'site_id', 'depth'. You can override using the `.groups` argument.
#Calculate percent contribution
